Usain Bolt won 8 gold medals in 3 Olympics, and he only ran for less than 115 seconds on the track, earning $119 million dollars. That's an economy of effort. But for those 2 minutes, he trained for 20 years. That's an investment. THINK LONG TERM. PATIENCE PAYS.'.

node.text:
Patience gives us grit.⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
WE LIVE IN A WORLD that's driven by instant gratification.⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
The trouble with the expectation for fast results is that some things require patience, persistence, and time to manifest.⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⠀
The positive effects of patience and persistence can go a long way in helping a person achieve success in business.⁣⁣⠀
